Turkey Aims to Create 20,000 Jobs in Diyarbakir, Sabah Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-16T06:00:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/turkey-aims-to-create-20-000-jobs-in-diyarbakir-sabah-reports.html
  Turkey ’s government began an
program of investment designed to create 20,000 jobs in
Diyarbakir, the biggest city in the mainly-Kurdish southeast of
the country, Sabah newspaper reported.  The project involves the conversion of disused government-
owned buildings into a textiles center and connection of local
industrial zones to natural gas supplies and rail lines, the
newspaper reported, citing Industry Minister Nihat Ergun.
There’ll also be a flower-processing center that will mainly
employ women, it said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
